result.execSummary:
The defendant Dakota S Tuckwab was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 3rd Degree Sexual Assault, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.225(3).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes:
The defendant must maintain/obtain full time employment/school that consists of at least 35 hrs/week.

When not full time employed/school, the defendant must apply for at least 3 jobs per week and report progress monthly to P&P with pertinent information in regards to applications.  The defendant must only apply for jobs qualified for - must accept any job offered - must not engage in any conduct that could result in the termination of his/her employment/school.

The defendant may not consume or possess alcohol.

The defendant may not have any contact with the victim (J.E.).

The defendant must submit a DNA sample.

The defendant must comply with sex offender registration contrary to 301.45 and Court finds it is mandatory reporting.

supervisions.notes:
Court has no objections to the defendant being able to visit with his child while incarcerated in the WI State Prison System.
To any sentence that the defendant is currently serving.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Dakota S Tuckwab in court with attorney Brian F. Bennett.  Defendant Dakota S Tuckwab in custody.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 9:55 AM. State is willing to amend #1 to 3rd degree sexual assault contrary to 940.225(3) also deleting repeater allegation (class G felony) and DRI #2, joint recommendation for sentencing. State agrees - joint recommendation is 8 years in the WI State Prison System consisting of 3 years of initial confinement followed by 5 years of ES, concurrent to any sentence that the defendant is currently serving with credit to be discussed with mandatory reporting of sex offender registration. Tuckwab agrees. Recess to fill out plea questionnaire. Recalled at 10:37 AM with same appearances. Court has plea questionnaire. State and Bennett are prepared to proceed with plea. Court dismisses and reads in count #2. Court amends count #1 to 3rd degree sexual assualt contrary to 940.225(3) - reads new charge and penalty. Tuckwab pleads G to amended count #1. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constitutional rights and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State has complied with victim notification requirements and she does not wish to make a statement. State submits exhibits #1 - interview of victim, #2A - series of phone calls between the defendant and the victim, #2b - itemization of phone calls from exhibit #2A. Court receives exhibits #1, #2A and #2B after no objections - makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Bennett makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Tuckwab makes statement, remorseful. Court sentences the defendant to the following: count #1 - 8 years in the WI State Prison System consisting of 3 years of initial confinement followed by 5 years of ES - concurrent to any sentence that the defendant is currently serving, ES conditions include: comply with sex offender registration (301.45) - 15 year term and finds it is mandatory reporting, no possession of body armor (941.291), no possession of firearms, no voting rights, submit DNA sample with expunction rights given, costs - paid in 90 days/CO, imposes jury fees of $1683.38 - paid in 90 days/CO, no consumption of alcohol, no possession or consumption of alcohol, obtain/maintain full time employment/school, no contact with the victim (J.R.E.), credit for 316 days, not eligible for any programs, right to appeal, Court has no objections to the defendant having visitation with is child, adjourned.

Defendant Dakota S Tuckwab in court with attorney Brian F. Bennett.  Defendant Dakota S Tuckwab in custody.   Charles Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 8:29 AM. Tuckwab does not have street clothes. Bennett indicates family will be making arrangement to get street clothes for Tuckwab. Bennet continues motion for adjournment and asks for adjournment for stated reasons, explains there was an agreement, was then rejected by DA, Brown County was on lock down and unable to discuss trial with his defendant, 6th amendment rights, right to deny counsel issue. Court does not agree and feels ample time to resolve case rather than a week before jury trial. State - rejected his offer in April, states why offer was rejected and still continues that rejected offer. Bennet responds. Court  - reviews offers/emails and feels DE never agreed to resolution, Bennet had not informed his client of agreement. Bennet responds. Court responds and denies motion to adjourn, inform jury it will be a little bit due to complications (getting clothes for DE) and possible resolution. Court will adjourn until later this afternoon and will talk with jury. Bennet does not feel the State would not come to an agreement. Bennet brings up juror to be released is victims father. Carter indicates he was a special juror for the last case and is not a juror today. State asks for JT to be excused as a juror as well duing to being a dispatcher. Court will allow JT to be excused. Bennet questions court on amended witness list filed by the State. State makes statement in regards to typo on witness list and will be calling 3 witnesses. Court will talk with jury. Carter asks is there will be an alternate juror. Court will pick an alternate juror due to possibly proceeding into tommorrow. Court will adjourn until 12:30 PM.
